<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1399] Lock settings are ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1399</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To reproduce: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;set dataDir to point to a directory that the current user has no access right to (/solr/data,  for non-root user, for example)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;change lockType to single&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;start example web server.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The server fails with the following error message that indicates that it still uses SimpleFSLock&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caused by: java.io.IOException: Cannot create directory: /solr/data/index&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.lucene.store.SimpleFSLock.obtain(SimpleFSLockFactory.java:138)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.lucene.store.Lock.obtain(Lock.java:73)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.lucene.index.IndexWriter.init(IndexWriter.java:1540)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.lucene.index.IndexWriter.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(IndexWriter.java:1310)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.solr.update.SolrIndexWriter.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(SolrIndexWriter.java:160)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.solr.core.SolrCore.initIndex(SolrCore.java:388)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran into this issue using custom DirectoryFactory. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
